{{Infobox artist | name = Abdul Vas | image = Abdul Vas 1.jpg | caption = Abdul Vas, 2012 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1981|03|15|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Maracay]], [[Venezuela]] | nationality = [[Venezuela]] | field = [[Contemporary art]], [[Painting]], [[Drawing]], [[Rock n' Roll]], [[Installation art]], [[Sculpture]] | training = [[Gerrit Rietveld Academie]] | works = | patrons = | influenced by = [[AC/DC]], [[MLB]], [[Marc Chagall]], [[Mike Kelley (artist)|Mike Kelley]], [[James Ensor]], [[Al Feldstein]], [[Brian Johnson]], [[Hieronymus Bosch]], [[Angus Young]] | influenced = | awards = | movement = [[Contemporary art]] }}
'''Abdul Vas''' (born 15 March 1981 in [[Maracay]], [[Venezuela]]) is a contemporary artist. He grew up living between [[Surinam]], [[Guyana]], and [[Belgium]]. After studies at EAVRA in Maracay and at the [[Gerrit Rietveld Academie]] in [[Amsterdam]] he lives and works in Amsterdam and [[Madrid]].<ref>[http://arcthemagazine.com/arc/2013/03/abdul-vas-shoot-to-thrill-curated-by-alexis-callado-estefania-casado-santapau-gallery-madrid/ Abdul Vas’ Shoot to Thrill-Curated by Alexis Callado Estefania-Casado Santapau Gallery] [[ARC Magazine]]</ref> He has created handmade [[books]] and [[zines]], [[photographs]], [[collages]], [[drawings]], [[paintings]] and [[murals]].
Vas's work has been discussed and reviewed in ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'',<ref>Pete Benesch. [https://www.vice.com/es/read/abdul-vas-acdc-stage/ Abdul Vas "Horror Movies, Anal Sex, Roosters, Trucks and AC/DC Have Always Made A Fiendishly Fun Combination."] Vice Magazine</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'',<ref>Antonio Fraguas. [http://rollingstone.es/specials/view/asi-es-el-profeta-de-ac-dc/ Asi Es El Profeta De AC/DC] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220030121/http://rollingstone.es/specials/view/asi-es-el-profeta-de-ac-dc/ |date=December 20, 2013 }} Rolling Stone</ref> [[ABC (newspaper)]],<ref>Paloma Torres. [http://www.abc.es/cultura/cultural/20130326/abci-arte-entrevista-abdul-201303261955.html/ Abdul Vas: "Mis Cuadros Estan Demasiado Relajados"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224175646/http://www.abc.es/cultura/cultural/20130326/abci-arte-entrevista-abdul-201303261955.html/ |date=December 24, 2013 }} ABC</ref> [[Esquire (magazine)]],<ref>Clara Montagut. [http://www.esquire.es/blogs/esquire-art-department/pollos-dominaran-tierra_489.html/ Y los pollos dominaran la tierra...] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130719013451/http://www.esquire.es/blogs/esquire-art-department/pollos-dominaran-tierra_489.html/ |date=July 19, 2013 }} Esquire</ref> and ''[[The New York Times]]''.<ref>Helen A. Harrison. [https://www.nytimes.com/2004/02/15/nyregion/art-reviews-private-expressions-speaking-to-the-world.html?pagewanted=2&src=pm/ Private Expressions, Speaking to the World] New York Times</ref> In 2009, he was selected for the Beijing Biennale.<ref>[http://www.theartistnetwork.org/798Biennale09/artists.htm/ Beijing Biennale Artists] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130119101444/http://www.theartistnetwork.org/798Biennale09/artists.htm/ |date=January 19, 2013 }}</ref> His works are part of various collections internationally, and have been exhibited throughout the [[United States]], [[Latin America]], [[Asia]] and [[Europe]].
== Work ==
Abdul Vas work broaches heavily the obsessions of his home country Venezuela with the symbols of the American dream. Heavily influenced by [[Marc Chagall]], [[Mike Kelley (artist)|Mike Kelley]], [[Al Feldstein]] and [[James Ensor]], Vas's work heavily consists of depictions of aggressive and well-hung [[rooster]]s that represent the masculine element of the American cowboy-culture. Therefore, his pictures are full of references to the American baseball team [[Cincinnati Reds]], [[MLB]], [[Malcolm Young]], [[the Rolling Stones]], [[Slayer]], [[Metallica]], [[the Black Crowes]], [[Muddy Waters]], [[SUV]]s, [[rock and roll]] and the symbols of the North American imperialist power: the [[Navistar]] trucks. Another common theme in his work is the Australian rock group [[AC/DC]], particularly lead singer [[Brian Johnson]]. Many of his other artworks are named after AC/DC songs or albums.
