'''Heinrich Melzer''' (born 1873) was a German [[Spiritualism|spiritualist]] [[Mediumship|medium]].
Melzer was born in [[Dresden|Dresden, Germany]]. For thirty years he gave [[séance]]s and claimed to have the ability to materialize [[stone]]s and [[flower]]s.<ref>[http://www.answers.com/topic/heinrich-melzer Biography for Heinrich Melzer]</ref> In the séance room he would only materialize the flowers under the table, and as the table was not checked [[Skepticism|skeptic]]s accused him of simply hiding the flowers under the table before his séances. When the room was checked and [[scientific control]]s were introduced no flowers appeared. In 1926 Melzer was exposed as a fraud as he was caught with small stones attached to the back of his ears by flesh coloured tape.<ref>[[E. Clephan Palmer]]. (2003). ''The Riddle of Spiritualism''. Kessinger Publishing. pp. 35-39. {{ISBN|978-0766179318}}</ref>
