'''Louis Brouillard''' (July 27, 1921 – October 10, 2018) was an American Catholic [[Priesthood (Catholic Church)|priest]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.desertsun.com/story/news/nation-now/2018/05/05/guam-priests-brouillard-profile/400594002/ | title=Priest accused in 124 Guam sex abuse cases ages quietly, alone}}</ref> involved in high-profile [[Catholic Church sexual abuse cases]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.pressreader.com/usa/usa-today-us-edition/20180507/281552291489915 | title=PressReader.com - Connecting People Through News}}</ref>
==Sexual abuse== Brouillard was ordained December 17, 1948, and served in priesthood on [[Guam]] from 1948 to 1981, and teaching at San Vicente and [[Father Dueñas Memorial School]] while he was a priest.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/world/world-news/priest-says-he-was-told-to-say-prayers-for-abusing-boys-sexual-abuse-assault-guam-2957554/|title=Priest says he was told to say prayers for abusing boys|date=6 August 2016|publisher=|accessdate=19 October 2018}}</ref> After which<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.radionz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/350833/sex-abuse-claim-against-guam-church-brings-total-lawsuits-to-157 | title=Sex abuse claim against Guam church brings total lawsuits to 157| date=2018-02-20}}</ref> he was accused of abusing more than 130 boys in sex abuse claims brought against the Catholic Church.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ncronline.org/news/accountability/guams-day-reckoning-after-decades-sex-abuse|title=Guam's day of reckoning after decades of sex abuse|date=4 October 2017|publisher=|accessdate=19 October 2018}}</ref> A lawsuit was filed against him as recently as six days prior to his death.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.desertsun.com/story/news/nation-now/2018/10/11/father-louis-brouillard-guam-dies-97/1610361002/ | title=Retired priest, accused in more than 130 sex abuse cases, dies at 97}}</ref> Lawsuits were also brought against the [[Boy Scouts of America]], because Brouillard was a scoutmaster.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.guampdn.com/story/news/2017/10/18/lawsuit-priest-lured-boys-into-homosexual-lifestyle-smoking/774901001/ | title=Lawsuit: Priest lured boys into homosexual lifestyle, smoking}}</ref> Brouillard's victims' accounts ranged from being molested during swimming trips to rape.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://pacificnewscenter.com/pedophile-priest-louis-brouillard-dead-at-97/ | title=Pedophile priest Louis Brouillard dead at 97 &#124; PNC News First}}</ref> According to Brouillard, while church members knew about his actions then, they did not tell him to stop, but rather to pray. In 1981, he was sent away to Minnesota,<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/priest-child-sex-abuse-pope-francis-punishment-pray-hail-mary-guam-a7178416.html | title=Priest who molested 20 boys told to say Hail Mary to make up for it| date=2016-08-08}}</ref> and ended up living in [[Pine City, Minnesota]] serving a nearby parish,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.startribune.com/minnesota-priest-accused-of-abusing-60-boys-in-guam/481834121/ | title=Minnesota priest accused of abusing 60 boys in Guam}}</ref> St. Joseph in [[Beroun, Minnesota|Beroun]], until he was barred from doing so in 1984.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.tcpalm.com/story/news/nation-now/2018/10/11/father-louis-brouillard-guam-dies-97/1610361002/ | title=Retired priest, accused in more than 130 sex abuse cases, dies at 97}}</ref> He lived in Pine City, and his legal deposition was held there October 31 through November 3, 2017, when he was 96. He admitted to as many as 20 of the incidents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.guampdn.com/story/news/2018/10/12/father-louis-brouillard-dies-97/1609502002/|title=Louis Brouillard dies at 97|publisher=|accessdate=19 October 2018}}</ref>
